A developer has defied the National Environmental Management Authority orders to stop construction of residential houses along Kunde Road in Thompson estate, Lavington.In a letter dated August 9, Nema ordered Pyramid Builders Ltd to stop further construction until an appeal lodged by the residents' association is determined by the National Environmental Tribunal.But the developer claims to have obtained court orders to proceed with the construction.Through Kunde Road Residents Welfare Association, residents are appealing to the government to intervene as the developer has moved heavy machinery to the site and is cutting down trees.The residents urged Nema to enforce its directive as they fear the developer will destroy the habitat. Despite the stop order, the respondent has continued to disobey and has continued felling down tress and demolishing existing structures. The developer has started moving heavy machinery into the site, reads the letter dated September 20 from lawyer Kimani Waweru.